</p></sec><sec><title>Blood loss and transfusion requirement</title><p>Blood loss in TXA group was significantly lower than that in control group in all measurement methods (DBL, THL, and CTBL) as shown in <xref ref-type="table" rid="T3">Table 3</xref>. Blood transfusion requirement in TXA group was also significantly lower than the control group with relative risk as 0.13 (95% confidence interval: 0.02&#x02013;0.92). Accumulated drainage volume in TXA group was significantly lower than that in control group all the recorded time after clamp release (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="F2">Figure 2</xref>). DBLR in TXA group was also significantly lower than that of control group in the first 6 hours after release a clamp (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="F3">Figure 3</xref>).</p><p>
